[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Inspecting class loader issues**\n\nI’m considering whether I can include older org.h2.Driver methods in reflect, but I'm facing a dynamic class loader issue. I need to look at the build wrapper because the native tests need to pass. Maybe I could use try assert thrown if it's native, but there's no guard there. I want to check if loadH2 fails after invoking the method since failures are unacceptable in native. It seems like Native Image supports URLClassLoader but doesn’t allow defining new classes at runtime. That could definitely lead to UnsupportedFeatureError. So, what if I choose a version not found in the map, allowing a custom ClassLoader fallback?\n\n**Exploring fake jar creation**\n\nI’m thinking about creating a fake jar in my local Maven repository for version 2.1.218 that excludes org/h2/Driver. This way, when cl.loadClass is called, it would use findClass and fallback to the system ClassLoader to load \"org.h2.Driver.\" Then, I can invoke the load method on the current H2 Driver, covering dynamic call sites. However, this approach feels a bit hacky since I'm manipulating m2 and using a malformed jar. I guess if it gets the job done without direct reflection, it might be acceptable. But, does using a null checksum for version 218 make the fake jar valid?\n\n**Considering ClassLoader and metadata**\n\nIn a native environment, a custom ClassLoader can load the system class if the class is known statically. I’m thinking that to use getDeclaredMethod and invoke on org.h2.Driver, I would need the proper metadata. Should an agent be able to collect and copy this metadata? However, I realize we shouldn’t execute anything. The existing reflect-config only has constructors for org.h2.Driver, not its methods. I wonder if the native compile will require reflection configuration for the load/unload methods since the test involves H2's reflection.\n\n**Checking metadata for workflow**\n\nI'm thinking about whether we might need to get metadata from the agent later. It seems like the workflow could run some sort of generation. I wonder if I need to edit the reflect-config to include methods. There's also a dynamic access report indicating that some metadata might be missing. I'll need to assess if we should add test resources, since these would be test-only metadata. I should also check if the library's metadata includes methods.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0de53abe6bfddf3d0169f1094ebdac8191ae87e20b884c1344\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8QlZPxAfq2zyQqTv1QpYe6iMInW5GnmWP5yaHy9OtDMtpqPrn5InLRSlD-u_-2fWoaMV8pqutvkWT92v5Z28ntATiJqvrQBWupKHcZw9mHOp6O06EzmS-JOS6yGWFcHtvJJ1Cfk96MC_n2PB8ESdYKz6hpjAjL09mHLJuiYx5F-iwuYS5QaJu1nTn-yAwF-Ix0wnEyO0wTNCptZhC-tEMsPsm4oXyK0k2kM7vRiNGVMJ0xjUI9ppGG7FMIqm5-lqp_rCCrnEel_KiFpOjGDF8Wd936evUB_j921HJKGfrvMPEjQK-7pE4jxHKq3jK75bWyzOCPi98QqfAh-Boc2u2cw7UP_wtI6eS_UhqNNAuUkQj_pmnX9YM8P2i4zqdXTTKSORif0rxreamvs-PKSz7_z4jh0B4xrbAVLLYAxdmZHRhaSPaSk0Jqv_DEIiweiozglubPDT4kthApr-0X3krDi9ApCuMNj16Fez5USN_i4zC5yQlN93BATxuUfeijfvzxOUS0kg6drJzakrtM6vlMwAldJGeYnDFtOMHr6NYs-kC99IBaEFBl5ucmNmWFA3eW_4hIk2PzHhbzZI4M4M7phtuCgJfQAdkzEsoI0RdMHIHoEKjkqumBGe9igygObytRr4oVW1R8HxjdyxKUBUV2X621MixHvNDRClii5ibis6xqP-xsT2T1dHRR3tmy_-5YdRqlHUooD4sPrC7tyBP5i3b8-qcnyWcwNj_a2Xvqoxc9y6NuoSC38JXxAlsLEsH-Sw1tKrozsOjTFGwdjHVUzPiA9EPvFi-s72kON7KVmldGWjIjnDRZ6MWD5nbFTI5ygUwh-rnidrUNq2CDS4Us0j3dPMt12Awuig993FGuM1Cc2ohKrbQLS-7IDjDgIHBsmHX3Ul5-49Qxl7Z6EttYQLh2WtAgjUuaWEUbpjieb_Nf6ZmL-YPp9522a_scW7JYuydZfhDun7A2ABQvwto2VAPUzgARJR0LCwMeNbzsXeJUM5YIepT3CFttcHylmUZYuKl2_sTAFXn8rHJwU0-Xna6mSy4FGqzs39MK7FyzFAIevm9c3rS8VCx82KYFCiPCgz--j2qo1CYYFb1sJLH0tgU5X3VjGEAYaa9uWFsC4DD3_LD-CjDf5M44y_dM2zWSxrAKo6P02svJ9b5SZ175v6Z4zOufRn53hEvYWDtbVgYMt_GUQ-kne71rEnsrX3Zs0tiCgRe71-K5j1AXV0jIBBM5MAKk0_ExWUNhD1MZ9-hAgZ7zpS4urEV_rnOnqI8BL1yEdQoBqHP0oyAbVWeHrB2MsnRU2J27AkNQ-8_5lkZeiOpsOjTtxt9Ekbgd7UXX8CT5igCIG1BqQszGE4HnEVPG-Sh2h