yPhvSg8ahrR2n6oAeu2i0bhbrPodDOvHq7qq4pEluL6vCe849h_CBirrwGY1PRBC3R2D0d_8oLL47vyUgZiSiucQs9Cg6bzo2oVINHZXEq7UftCzNbAXE-ntbVOInlKsFuclbCSaTBLulttUIqC8gQHtPZ30GW6tXYTe5RlDkIOvpD8Ze0ha4hXdfxKm_SWGS5KENGkEg1kUuz97cS_iXN3kjy4PvYYBQqoadVtsnFxLiyR07Oaq-SfBTZBmDBVrZ4aiydFJyNgDv7i2aYgGCee8LmcmVSUQScOkr0EM452_yXZqJg-U00x5b1b9l3oE-J-uekz2OnltdmeUFpCY--3Fq4vyXQVLjKB7LMTjpEmdnbXuspRcPJmNvStZimaW4Dbr1ac4BJFyGg26Sq8NHye1oau373ujI5rMAPkeQs-V5vqJlKMl4NxJbuh1mI5Ot15S3mN8vF4CfRzyGs3-eqoTzj5q03Ajp7RmFTz10EdHkA5ayIRCUgwYy60b69MpdQwwccs63BU6nQwoIn-KPpTnyT6Ma18gZW-4c_KVu0Y9f514e6rz2JxcSe_IEi2ZB72rvFi9QoQdRUPUBOFs6RaPRBeP_Bn3izfjqtYBCs2AMVWBs77b2n8Q-imfVdGhWJlm8ML_yBy1q2MrEpyn_ZFnXGh4FAe6mVkHUvK-4BrB-J8SvkkeODRJt-WcmoH6xrf-2hLavGQmTCKTOlA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering jar creation process**\\n\\nI need to create a test jar and am wondering if writing directly to user.home is okay. It should be OS-independent, and I want to ensure any legitimate jar isn’t deleted. If it exists, it can’t be overwritten. In CI, there might be a real version due to prior dependencies, so I guess I should pick a rare checksum option if there’s a risk. I’m contemplating backing up before restoring after testing— a better approach. Setting user.home to a temporary directory could work. That might help avoid issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing jar creation and class loading**\\n\\nI've got a valid version, 2.1.8, where the checksum is null and computes an index that looks good! I need to create a zip or jar with a minimal entry, maybe a \\\"placeholder.txt.\\\" I'm thinking about using ZipInputStream but also facing some class loading issues with the custom loader. It seems I need to ensure the org.h2.Driver is correctly accessed and asserted. I want to avoid global side effects, so unloading and deregistering the driver is essential. I’m considering JUnit order and how it affects the tests that need H2.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering driver unloading effects**\\n\\nIf I unload the H2 driver during the test, I might run into issues with subsequent tests not being able to access it through DriverManager unless it's re-registered. I can call Driver.load() afterward to address this issue. However, I need to consider that unloadH2 itself might invoke unload on the system driver if the fallback to the fake jar is activated. I need to be cautious here to avoid breaking subsequent tests.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_7zE4JWwIAWbqtZGsFBLRzESb|fc_0de53abe6bfddf3d0169f109796dec819189d7e50f98dc26e0", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java/h2/UpgradeTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage h2;\n\nimport org.h2.Driver;\nimport org.h2.tools.Upgrade;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.sql.DriverManager;\nimport java.util.jar.JarEntry;\nimport java.util.jar.JarOutputStream;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class UpgradeTest {\n    private static final int H2_VERSION_WITHOUT_CHECKSUM = 218;\n\n    @TempDir\n    Path userHome;\n\n    @Test\n    void loadAndUnloadH2DriverThroughUpgradeTool() throws Exception {\n        Path h2Jar = userHome.resolve(Path.of(\".m2\", \"repository\", \"com\", \"h2database\", \"h2\", \"2.1.218\",\n                \"h2-2.1.218.jar\"));\n        Files.createDirectories(h2Jar.getParent());\n        writeMinimalH2Jar(h2Jar);\n\n        String previousUserHome = System.getProperty(\"user.home\");\n        System.setProperty(\"user.home\", userHome.toString());\n        java.sql.Driver driver = null;\n        try {\n            driver = Upgrade.loadH2(H2_VERSION_WITHOUT_CHECKSUM);\n\n            assertThat(driver).isInstanceOf(Driver.class);\n        } finally {\n            if (driver != null) {\n                Upgrade.unloadH2(driver);\n                Driver.load();\n            }\n            if (previousUserHome != null) {\n                System.setProperty(\"user.home\", previousUserHome);\n            } else {\n                System.clearProperty(\"user.home\");\n            }\n        }\n\n        assertThat(DriverManager.getDriver(\"jdbc:h2:mem:upgrade-test\")).isInstanceOf(Driver.class);\n    }\n\n    private static void writeMinimalH2Jar(Path h2Jar) throws Exception {\n        try (JarOutputStream jar = new JarOutputStream(Files.newOutputStream(h2Jar))) {\n            jar.putNextEntry(new JarEntry(\"placeholder.txt\"));\n            jar.write(\"fallback to runtime H2 driver\".getBytes());\n            jar.closeEntry();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 759, "output": 1509, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35548, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777404259421, "responseId": "resp_0de53abe6bfddf3d0169f10963f54c819189302eb4e9416508"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_7zE4JWwIAWbqtZGsFBLRzESb|fc_0de53abe6bfddf3d0169f109796dec819189d7e50f98dc26e0", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2095 bytes to tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/src/test/java/h2/UpgradeTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777404282813}]}
